SIMPLE: outness
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Outness
<hw>Out"ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state
of being out or beyond; separateness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metaph.)</fld> <def>The state or quality of being
distinguishable from the perceiving mind, by being in space, and
possessing material quality; externality; objectivity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>outness</qex> of the objects of sense.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
W. Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Outnoise</ent>⟦br⟧
